During President Bush's visit to Iraq, a journalist threw shoes at him, symbolizing the conflicted views towards the war.
Despite the chaos, Bush remained calm, joking about the incident.
The shoe-throwing highlighted the ongoing opposition to his policies.
Bush emphasized progress in Iraq and the security agreement as he nears the end of his presidency.
The incident, while dramatic, did not deter Bush from his mission.
This unexpected event underscored the complexities and challenges faced in Iraq, encapsulating the mixed emotions towards the outgoing president.
